    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-11-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="678" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d678">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 770.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 30, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 13th of November (No.
                            535) has been received. The President is gratified with the reception
                            which Earl Russell has given to my suggestions in regard to obtaining a
                            sanction, by the Mikado, of the treaties which have been made by the
                            western powers with the Tycoon of Japan. The latest information received
                            from Mr. Pruyn induces a hope that the efforts of the daimios, under the
                            Mikado’s patronage, to expel foreigners from the country will not be
                            continued.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">C. F. Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
